<question-stem>
<para> According to the professor, what are some of the features of writing?<mediaExhibit
frameType="mp3" mediaRef="toeflPrac10233.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set multipleAnswer="yes">
<answer-choice correct="yes"> It uses punctuation to aid comprehension</answer-choice>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> It uses longer and more complex sentences than
spoken language.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> It often reflects the era in which it was written.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> It allows for information to be communicated with fewer errors
than speech does.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> It is often directed to an unknown audience.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The professor states specifically that <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> we
rely on punctuation marks to aid comprehension </emphasis>(A). She also states
that "the sentences are<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>often longer
and more complex" (B), and that "writing is often<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>directed
to an unknown audience" (E). (C) is incorrect because it is<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>not
mentioned as a feature of writing. And (D) is incorrect because<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>it
does not specifically mention the type of error (that is, grammatical mistakes).</para>
</explanation>
